06025nam a22006135i 9780774856706DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t19901990xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807748567067 a10.59962/97807748567062doi  a(DE-B1597)661116  a(OCoLC)748214646  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aHD1491.P4bK67 1990eb 7aPOL0000002bisacsh04a334.683qOCoLC1 aKorovkin, Tanya, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aPolitics of Agricultural Co-Operativism :bPeru, 1969-1983 /cTanya Korovkin. 1aVancouver ;aToronto : bUniversity of British Columbia Press, c[1990] 4c©1990  a1 online resource (195 p.) :b25 tables  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tTables -- tAbbreviations -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tAgricultural Co-Operativism: A National Perspective -- tAgricultural Co-Operatives Under Military Populism 1969–1975 -- tCo-Operatives in the Post-Populist Context 1975–1983 -- tThe Cotton Co-Operatives: A History of Success and Failure -- tThe Origin and Socio-Economic Organization of the Cotton Co-Operatives -- tCo-Operative Institutions: Internal Participation and External Political Involvement -- tCo-Operative Economy in Crisis -- tCo-Operative Responses to the Economic Crisis -- tConclusion -- tAppendices -- tAppendix 1 -- tAppendix 2 -- tAppendix 3 -- tAppendix 4 -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book is a detailed analysis of the evolution of state-sponsored agricultural co-operativism in Peru, an Andean country with high levels of land concentration and widespread rural poverty. Most Peruvian agricultural co-operatives were organized during the military populist government of Velasco Alvarado which, after radical land reform, transformed expropriated estates into co-operatives. From the start, these projects became subject to multiple pressures that ranged from unfavourable government economic policies -- designed to promote import-substitution industrialization at the expense of the agricultural sector -- to the growth of the co-operative bureaucracy and the deterioration of labour discipline. A shift toward market-oriented economic strategies after the fall of the Velasco government aggravated the co-operatives' difficulties. Stabilization programs implemented by Velasco's successor, General Mortales Bermudez, and liberalization of the national economy by the civilian government of Belaunder Terry dealt a severe blow to Peru's co-operative agriculture. The ensuing crisis gave rise to political mobilization against the market-oriented economic policies. However, the effectiveness of this movement was undermined by a trend toward dissolution of agricultural co-operatives by many members who turned to individual/private agriculture as a solution. Korovkin examines not only the diverging responses of co-operative memebers to the crisis, but also the external policy-related and internal organizational causes behind it. The focus of this book is on the cotton-growing sector that constituted the back-bone of the state-sponsored co-operative movement in Peru. The analysis of the national dynamic is complemented by case studies of three cotton estates converted into agricultural production co-operatives. One of these proved reasonably successful, while the other two experienced serious economic difficulties, looking for their solution in either poitical mobilization against the government's economic policies or in the shift to individual/private agriculture. The comparative analysis of their experiences provides valuable insights into the nature of organizational problems confronting Peru's co-operative movement. Korovkin also places the discussion of the Peruvian co-operative experience in a broader historical and theoretical perspective, focusing on the changing nature of social alliances and economic strategies during the populist and post-populist periods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculture and state -- Peru -- History -- 20th century. 0aAgriculture and statezPeruxHistoryy20th century. 0aAgriculture and statezPeru. 0aAgriculture, Cooperative -- Peru -- History -- 20th century. 0aAgriculture, CooperativezPeruxHistoryy20th century. 0aCotton growing -- Peru -- History -- 20th century. 0aCotton growingzPeruxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311141940440uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485670640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774856706423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774856706/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141940-4  University of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles